The quiet insight behind your point

Humans are not just storytelling animals—we are story-sharing networks.

Ideas move through these networks, sometimes fading quickly and sometimes becoming part of the long-term cultural landscape.

The stories that persist tend to be those that align strongly with human cognition and social needs.

